## Release Gate

- Retry-state leakage is a blocker.
- Admin dry-run cannot queue records.
- Rollback steps must be precise enough for on-call use.
--- incident_context/recovery-checklist.md
## Recovery Checklist

Before retrying the cutover:
- prove rollback leaves rows at `pending` after forced failures
- prove dry-run stays read-only
- document the rollback steps for operators
--- incident_context/retry-state-rollback.md
## Incident 2026-04-07

The prior SQLAlchemy 2 cutover was rolled back after a failed worker retry left
rows in `processing` and the admin dry-run path queued real work. The incident
was not caused by `select()` itself; it was caused by preserving legacy helper
commits across the retry and planning flows.

