Plan:
1. Remove repository-owned commits and switch repository reads to SQLAlchemy 2 `select()` patterns.
2. Put the worker and admin paths on real operation-level transactions so failures roll back the whole unit of work and dry-run stays non-persistent.
3. Make the API layer safe to use either inside an existing session or as a top-level boundary when given a session factory.
4. Rewrite the cutover note so it documents the retry-state incident, the new rollback behavior, and the operator recovery checks.
5. Run the requested `pytest` target and verify the final state.
