Implemented the SQLAlchemy 2 modernization in the allowed files only. Repository access now uses `select()` and no longer commits inside helpers, so transaction ownership stays with the caller in [app/repository.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v5-recovery-in-thread-run2/workspace/app/repository.py:1). The worker and admin flows now use operation-level boundaries so failures roll back the whole unit of work, and admin dry-runs explicitly discard staged queue changes instead of leaking retry state into the database in [app/worker.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v5-recovery-in-thread-run2/workspace/app/worker.py:4) and [app/admin_cli.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v5-recovery-in-thread-run2/workspace/app/admin_cli.py:4). I also made the API usable either inside an existing session or as a top-level boundary when given a session factory in [app/api.py](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v5-recovery-in-thread-run2/workspace/app/api.py:1).

The deploy note now reflects the rollback incident and the recovery expectations instead of preserving the legacy helper-commit model, in [docs/deploy/sqlalchemy2-cutover.md](/Users/zhiyuanma/work/CursorWS/Lumo_FlyWheel/verifier_data/sqlalchemy-2-session-modernization/_probe_workdirs/attempt_04_live_probe/v5-recovery-in-thread-run2/workspace/docs/deploy/sqlalchemy2-cutover.md:1).

Validation: `pytest -q tests/test_api.py tests/test_worker.py tests/test_admin_cli.py` passed (`3 passed`). There was one non-fatal `PytestCacheWarning` because pytest could not write `.pytest_cache` outside the writable sandbox.
